heading_context: Get free vehicle tax if you're a driver with a disability
chunks.html_content:
You may not have to pay vehicle tax if either:

  • you’re a disabled driver
  • you have a certain type of vehicle
chunks.plain_content:
Get free vehicle tax if you're a driver with a disability

heading_context: Get free vehicle tax if you're a driver with a disability
chunks.html_content: You can only use your exemption on one vehicle at a time. If you have more than one vehicle, you’ll need to choose which one will be exempt from vehicle tax.
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Get free vehicle tax if you're a driver with a disability
If you’re applying for the first time
chunks.html_content:
If you have a used vehicle, you need to go to a Post Office branch that deals with vehicle tax.

To find a Post Office branch, you can either:

  • use the Post Office branch finder - choose ‘Vehicle tax’ from the menu
  • call the Post Office - ask for your nearest branch that deals with vehicle tax

heading_context: Get free vehicle tax if you're a driver with a disability
Refunds on your current vehicle tax
chunks.html_content: You’ll automatically get a refund for any full remaining months of vehicle tax when you apply for exemption. The refund will be sent to the address the DVLA have on their records.

heading_context: Get free vehicle tax if you're a driver with a disability
Check which vehicles you do not need to pay tax on
chunks.html_content:
You do not have to pay tax on some types of vehicle, for example:

  • disabled passenger vehicles

  • mobility vehicles and powered wheelchairs.

Check which types of vehicles are exempt from vehicle tax.
